00:23:35,800 --> 00:23:39,900
When I travel to a new place, I'm used to recording it on the travel app.

261
00:23:43,600 --> 00:23:45,200
Want to eat some?

262
00:24:06,800 --> 00:24:08,200
Thank you.

263
00:24:31,000 --> 00:24:33,000
- The thing is...
- The thing is...

264
00:24:36,800 --> 00:24:38,400
You first.

265
00:24:45,220 --> 00:24:48,260
Actually, you should switch majors.

266
00:24:52,400 --> 00:24:55,400
- But...
- But what?

267
00:25:02,400 --> 00:25:07,200
But... There's someone in our department I can't bear to leave.

268
00:25:20,200 --> 00:25:25,200
Wh-What I meant to say is... I have many friends in our department,

269
00:25:25,200 --> 00:25:27,800
and the teachers are also very nice to me.

270
00:25:27,800 --> 00:25:31,100
My grades have also improved a lot so...

271
00:25:34,400 --> 00:25:36,240
I studied architecture...

272
00:25:36,240 --> 00:25:39,000
because since I was a child, I always think that

273
00:25:39,000 --> 00:25:41,800
building houses is particularly interesting.

274
00:25:42,600 --> 00:25:45,600
It's not because my mom is an architect.

275
00:25:46,300 --> 00:25:51,200
In high school, you said you wanted to study fashion design.

276
00:25:51,200 --> 00:25:54,200
Your eyes sparkled when you said that.

277
00:25:55,700 --> 00:25:58,300
But now that you're in the Architecture Department,

278
00:25:59,600 --> 00:26:02,000
I can't see the same passion in you.

279
00:26:14,600 --> 00:26:16,200
Xia Miaomiao!

280
00:26:27,950 --> 00:26:32,350
- Go have some food.
- Okay.

281
00:26:43,800 --> 00:26:46,800
I... can get up on my own.

282
00:27:00,400 --> 00:27:03,400
What are you doing? Put me down.

283
00:27:03,400 --> 00:27:05,800
I'll dump you into the water if you keep on nagging.

284
00:27:05,800 --> 00:27:08,000
