285
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:09,260
There are nails on the bridge.

286
00:27:09,260 --> 00:27:11,000
What if you step on them?

287
00:27:16,200 --> 00:27:18,200
Don't get me wrong.

288
00:27:18,800 --> 00:27:23,600
I just think that... I bullied you too often in the past.

289
00:27:24,600 --> 00:27:27,000
To the point that you even wanted to switch majors.

290
00:27:28,200 --> 00:27:30,400
So, I should be nicer to you.

291
00:27:31,600 --> 00:27:34,100
I'm not switching majors because of you.

292
00:27:34,100 --> 00:27:36,400
Just put me down first.

293
00:27:36,400 --> 00:27:38,000
I'll put you down after we finish crossing the bridge.

294
00:27:38,000 --> 00:27:40,500
Keep fussing and I'll carry you on my shoulders.

295
00:27:43,800 --> 00:27:46,000
What kind of house are we staying in?

296
00:27:46,800 --> 00:27:49,400
It's the homestay owner's ancestral home.

297
00:27:49,400 --> 00:27:50,800
Is it very ancient?

298
00:27:50,800 --> 00:27:52,800
It's not.

299
00:27:52,800 --> 00:27:57,600
We'll have a chance to experience staying in a Chinese traditional building.

300
00:27:57,600 --> 00:28:00,100
How is it? We're here.

301
00:28:00,800 --> 00:28:03,100
This is surely some life experience.

302
00:28:04,200 --> 00:28:06,600
Let's go. What are we still waiting for?

303
00:28:06,600 --> 00:28:08,400
You're the one standing still, not us.

304
00:28:08,400 --> 00:28:09,400
Keep up.

305
00:28:09,400 --> 00:28:12,800
Don't be finicky. This is such a simple countryside..

306
00:28:12,800 --> 00:28:15,000
Who is being finicky?

307
00:28:27,800 --> 00:28:33,900
Miaomiao, these are the Doraemon flowers that you like, Liang Younian.

308
00:28:36,000 --> 00:28:40,200
Those flowers... were supposed to be given to me?

309
00:28:48,600 --> 00:28:50,900
Those were for me.

310
00:28:54,000 --> 00:28:56,400
Do you like staying in shabby houses that much?

311
00:29:00,600 --> 00:29:02,400
You're sick.

312
00:30:25,000 --> 00:30:26,600
Don't be scared.

313
00:30:26,600 --> 00:30:28,100
Senior.

314
00:30:29,000 --> 00:30:31,600
Did you just open the door just now?

315
00:30:32,410 --> 00:30:33,860
No.

316
00:30:35,330 --> 00:30:38,210
It's all right. I'll go take a look.

317
00:30:43,600 --> 00:30:46,000
Can I go with you?

318
00:30:59,800 --> 00:31:03,100
♪  If I have a fairy wand...  ♪

319
00:31:03,800 --> 00:31:06,600
♪  Make me bigger, smaller, and prettier  ♪

320
00:31:08,800 --> 00:31:11,100
♪  The toy car...  ♪

321
00:31:12,000 --> 00:31:14,000
I'm scared...

322
00:31:16,600 --> 00:31:20,700
♪  Chocolate and the toy car...  ♪

323
00:31:21,800 --> 00:31:24,700
♪  If I have a fairy wand  ♪

324
00:31:26,000 --> 00:31:27,500
What are you two doing?

325
00:31:27,500 --> 00:31:31,100
You're staying up at night to sing out here?

326
00:31:31,100 --> 00:31:33,200
Kaituo...

327
00:31:33,200 --> 00:31:36,600
There seemed to be someone outside just now.

328
00:31:52,800 --> 00:31:54,800
"A quiet conscience sleeps in thunder."

329
00:31:54,800 --> 00:31:56,620
"A quiet conscience sleeps in thunder."

330
00:31:56,620 --> 00:31:58,500
Brother Yuan....

331
00:32:01,570 --> 00:32:04,400
Brother Yuan...

332
00:32:05,790 --> 00:32:08,710
Brother Yuan...

333
00:32:08,710 --> 00:32:10,410
- Miaomiao.
- Yes?

334
00:32:10,410 --> 00:32:12,200
Stay here and don't go anywhere.

335
00:32:12,940 --> 00:32:15,340
Kaituo and I will go take a look first.

336
00:32:16,100 --> 00:32:19,200
I'm... scared of being by myself here.

337
00:32:19,200 --> 00:32:22,700
Can I... go together with you guys?

338
00:32:44,350 --> 00:32:47,260
Who is playing ghost out there?

339
00:32:47,260 --> 00:32:49,390
Come out now!

340
00:33:09,020 --> 00:33:11,250
Brother Yuan!

341
00:33:25,560 --> 00:33:28,430
Brother Yuan...

342
00:33:31,400 --> 00:33:34,230
Brother Yuan.

343
00:33:36,620 --> 00:33:39,260
Brother Yuan.

344
00:33:39,830 --> 00:33:40,740
[Lush Courtyard]

345
00:33:40,740 --> 00:33:43,600
Very good, you're all doing very well.

346
00:33:43,600 --> 00:33:46,860
"A day's plan lies in the morning." We should be efficient.

347
00:33:46,860 --> 00:33:49,690
Li Baiyang, efficiency.

348
00:33:49,690 --> 00:33:53,260
You, hurry up. Eat faster. Eat your buns faster.

349
00:33:53,260 --> 00:33:58,070
As for this field trip, we have to make models.

350
00:33:58,070 --> 00:34:03,900
Now, based on the measurements and sketches we made yesterday, we're going to be making models of the ancestral houses.

351
00:34:03,900 --> 00:34:07,200
I've grouped you randomly. Feel free to cooperate.

352
00:34:07,200 --> 00:34:12,550
When you're making models, be sure to coordinate the landscape with the building.

353
00:34:12,550 --> 00:34:15,130
- Understand?
- Yes, understood.

354
00:34:15,130 --> 00:34:17,500
Hurry up, get moving.

355
00:34:17,500 --> 00:34:19,950
- Be efficient. Hurry up.
- Yes.

356
00:34:19,990 --> 00:34:21,540
- Let's go.
- Hurry up. Go over there.

357
00:34:21,540 --> 00:34:23,110
- I can't eat anymore.
- Eat it up quickly.

358
00:34:23,110 --> 00:34:25,110
Hurry up.

359
00:34:33,510 --> 00:34:37,190
How do we start?

360
00:34:41,060 --> 00:34:44,700
You're good with color coordination and handiwork. You'll be in charge of the landscapes.

361
00:34:44,700 --> 00:34:47,760
- Kaituo and I will take care of the building itself.
- Sure.

362
00:34:47,760 --> 00:34:50,020
How come you get to delegate?

363
00:34:50,050 --> 00:34:53,220
I was unlucky enough to be on your team, but it doesn't make you the leader.

364
00:34:53,220 --> 00:34:56,700
Nor should I have to listen to you.

365
00:34:59,060 --> 00:35:03,340
Okay then, you can delegate. I'll listen to you, Team Leader.

366
00:35:09,630 --> 00:35:12,230
Split up and handle the materials first.

367
00:35:12,230 --> 00:35:13,820
All right.

368
00:35:36,940 --> 00:35:38,480
What?

369
00:35:45,350 --> 00:35:48,270
It's not this embroidery, too.

370
00:35:50,780 --> 00:35:54,590
Would it be a lost embroidery?

371
00:36:07,930 --> 00:36:10,850
Lend me two sandpapers. Thank you.

372
00:36:18,890 --> 00:36:22,450
Who told you to saw it?

373
00:36:22,450 --> 00:36:24,900
It's crooked. Give me the saw. I'll do it.

374
00:36:24,900 --> 00:36:27,680
I'll give it a go again. I can do this.

375
00:36:30,220 --> 00:36:33,840
There's only this much wood. There isn't enough for you to waste.

376
00:36:33,840 --> 00:36:35,420
Miaomiao.

377
00:36:36,710 --> 00:36:39,100
Try not to saw it vertically.

378
00:36:39,100 --> 00:36:43,310
Look at how I do it. Hold your saw a bit slanted. Try it.

379
00:36:55,640 --> 00:36:58,410
It really works.

380
00:37:08,730 --> 00:37:12,290
You're smiling? You won't smile when you hurt your hand.

381
00:37:45,650 --> 00:37:47,180
What's wrong?

382
00:37:47,180 --> 00:37:48,510
Nothing.

383
00:37:49,300 --> 00:37:51,230
What are you doing with that?

384
00:37:51,230 --> 00:37:53,850
I'm going to polish this.

385
00:37:53,870 --> 00:37:55,550
Give it to me.

386
00:37:56,280 --> 00:38:00,310
When you're done, I have to work on it again. I don't have that much time.

387
00:38:00,350 --> 00:38:04,070
I haven't done it yet. How do you know that I won't do it well?

388
00:38:04,070 --> 00:38:08,160
It goes without thinking. Look for materials for the landscape.

389
00:38:08,160 --> 00:38:10,070
- But—
- No "buts".

390
00:38:10,070 --> 00:38:13,400
I'm the team leader. You have to listen to me.

391
00:38:14,580 --> 00:38:16,830
Go on.

392
00:38:37,580 --> 00:38:41,060
Do you like Xia Miaomiao?

393
00:38:47,980 --> 00:38:49,860
How could I like Xia Miaomiao?

394
00:38:49,860 --> 00:38:53,090
Am I blind? She's just a trouble maker!

395
00:38:53,090 --> 00:38:55,650
Don't you find her dumb and foolish?

396
00:38:55,700 --> 00:38:58,470
She can't do anything well.

397
00:39:02,980 --> 00:39:05,420
I don't think so.

398
00:39:06,100 --> 00:39:09,310
Since the first day I met Xia Miaomiao,

399
00:39:09,310 --> 00:39:12,420
she was neither dumb nor foolish.

400
00:39:12,420 --> 00:39:16,630
She is adorable and kind.

401
00:39:41,550 --> 00:39:43,510
What?

402
00:39:47,970 --> 00:39:50,350
It's a match.

403
00:39:52,150 --> 00:39:54,820
- You gave me a fright.
- I'm sorry.

404
00:39:54,860 --> 00:39:57,200
- Do you want to stay here?
- No! No!

405
00:39:57,200 --> 00:40:00,350
No, I'd just like to ask who embroidered this portiere?

406
00:40:00,350 --> 00:40:01,990
This? My grandma did.

407
00:40:01,990 --> 00:40:04,310
Why?

408
00:40:05,190 --> 00:40:07,950
I'm a teacher at Haicheng University's Fashion Design Department.

409
00:40:07,950 --> 00:40:11,540
I would like to learn how to do this ancient embroidery. Can you take me to see her?

410
00:40:11,540 --> 00:40:12,940
Well...

411
00:40:12,940 --> 00:40:15,650
My grandma doesn't remember a thing now.

412
00:40:15,650 --> 00:40:18,410
She might not be of any help. How about this?

413
00:40:18,410 --> 00:40:20,340
I'll ask her.

414
00:40:20,340 --> 00:40:22,820
- Thank you.
- Don't mention it.

415
00:40:32,440 --> 00:40:33,700
What's wrong?

416
00:40:33,700 --> 00:40:35,390
My grandma is missing again.

417
00:40:35,390 --> 00:40:37,670
She went out once last night.

418
00:40:37,670 --> 00:40:39,610
Your students bought her home.

419
00:40:39,670 --> 00:40:42,310
- Where has she gone now?
- What should we do? Should we call the police?

420
00:40:42,310 --> 00:40:44,230
No need, no need.

421
00:40:45,180 --> 00:40:47,430
I'll check at our old house. She is often there.

